Greetings Fellow Java Junkies,

An awful case of child abuse from the state of Kansas has 
caused an increased sense of alert among its citizens and
officials.

Two foster parents are charged with the murder of their 9-year-
old child after he was found dead from suffocation. Now the 
state's welfare system is under investigation. Assuredly, many
are asking, "How could something like this happen?"

While in no way should this case be disregarded at any level,
the state of Kansas' foster care system has reported that only
one percent of children have been shown to be abused. However,
when such a case as this pops up, it prompts officials to 
investigate to find out if more incidents are occurring. 

Taking into account the horrible crime that was committed and
the statistic reported by the state, should an in-depth, and
likely costly, investigation take place?

